16/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- State officials and US representatives celebrated on Tuesday (March 15th) the 20th anniversary of the establishment of relations between the two countries.
At a ceremony at the foreign ministry, Prime Minister Sali Berisha said the US has played a decisive role in these two decades since the fall of communism.
US Ambassador Alexander Arvizu urged both countries "to look back in history to appreciate the achievements and define the path of the future".
In her message, US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton encouraged Albanians to work together to ensure the country makes progress, especially in terms of EU integration.
She also praised Tirana's contributions to the NATO force in Afghanistan.
(VoA, Top Channel, Balkan Web - 15/03/11)
